OL,3,CHow are schools prepared for
OL,4,Cemergencies?
OL,6,FEvery school is different in terms of
OL,7,Flocation, size and its pupils, which
OL,8,Fprevents a one-size-fits-all model
OL,9,Fworking for every institution.
OL,11,FEach school is therefore responsible
OL,12,Ffor creating its own system of how to
OL,13,Fhandle different types of emergency.
OL,15,FGlobally school security systems vary
OL,16,Fhugely based on what is most common in
OL,17,Fa particular country.
OL,19,FShooting lockdown drills are very
OL,20,Fcommon in countries , for example,
OL,21,Fsuch as in the United States.
